## Review Guidelines

### Correctness & Safety
- Uncaught exceptions; bare `except:`; wrong exception types
- Mutable default arguments; shared global state
- Hardcoded secrets, API keys, tokens in source

### Python / API
- Missing type hints on public APIs (when project uses typing)
- SQL injection via string formatting; unsafe `eval` / `pickle`
- Incorrect async usage (blocking calls in async code)

### Performance & Resources
- N+1 queries; loading entire tables into memory
- Unclosed files/sockets; missing context managers

### Testing & Maintainability
- Missing error handling on external I/O
- Breaking public API without migration notes

## Scoring

- **90-100**: Clean code, no significant issues
- **70-89**: Minor issues only
- **50-69**: Moderate issues
- **30-49**: Serious issues (security, data loss risk)
- **0-29**: Critical issues requiring immediate fix

